@startuml
' @id(USE-DEPLOY-GUIDANCE)
' @id(USE-DEPLOY-INSPECT)
' @id(USE-DEPLOY-DIALECT)
' @id(USE-DEPLOY-PURPOSE)
' @id(USE-DEPLOY-ACCESS-CHECK)
' @id(USE-DEPLOY-EXECUTE)
' @id(USE-DEPLOY-GOLIVE)
'
' Objective-side use cases for the /mdd-deploy utility skill. STANDALONE,
' a sibling of /mdd-render: NOT wired into /mdd-cycle, /mdd-map,
' /mdd-validate, or /mdd-review (it stays outside the parity gate).
'
' CHANGE (cycle 0021): /mdd-deploy is inverted from guidance-only into a
' FULL EXECUTOR. It still PLANS first (the dialect/purpose/access gates and
' the diagram + IaC + runbook are unchanged), then it EXECUTES the runbook
' end to end — managing cloud auth itself, dry-running, applying,
' provisioning, migrating, and routing traffic all the way to LIVE. It
' pauses for confirmation ONLY at irreversible steps and HALTS on the first
' failed step. Two new gates join the plan-phase gates:
'   - USE-DEPLOY-EXECUTE: walk the runbook autonomously, blocking only at
'     irreversible steps (first infra apply, secret writes, migration job,
'     go-live); halt on first error; new revision at 0% traffic until
'     health-verified.
'   - USE-DEPLOY-GOLIVE: before the production billing multi-factor cutover
'     and traffic routing, surface the FULL gate state and BLOCK for an
'     explicit operator confirmation — never auto-confirmed.
' The old "executes nothing / never runs az" non-goal is RETIRED.
'
' @desc(USE-DEPLOY-GUIDANCE, "Operator runs /mdd-deploy with a one-line deployment description; the skill PLANS (UML deployment diagram, secure-by-default generated IaC in the CONFIRMED dialect, and an explicit runbook that preserves the target's security invariants) and then EXECUTES that runbook end to end to live traffic — managing cloud auth, dry-running, applying, provisioning secrets, running the pre-traffic migration job, deploying the revision, and routing traffic. It pauses with a BLOCKING clarification on ambiguity and on any GENERALIZED landmine — any choice whose correctness depends on a fact not grounded in the inputs it read (app-config, purpose, access-path axes) — and during execution it pauses ONLY at irreversible steps, halting on the first failed step. It surfaces gaps and hardened-default trade-offs for the operator to decide instead of guessing.")
' @desc(USE-DEPLOY-INSPECT, "Operator inspects the generated deployment diagram visually: /mdd-render also rasterizes .mdd/deploy/**/*.puml to .mdd/rendered/deploy/**/*.svg. Additive and non-gating.")
' @desc(USE-DEPLOY-DIALECT, "Before any deploy artifact is created, /mdd-deploy resolves the requested IaC dialect (Bicep or Terraform), presents it back, and BLOCKS for an explicit operator confirmation. No silent default; exactly one dialect per run; Terraform enforces the same invariants + secure-by-default posture as Bicep, differing only in structure (main.tf + modules + azurerm provider + remote state backend).")
' @desc(USE-DEPLOY-PURPOSE, "Before any purpose-driven default is generated, /mdd-deploy establishes the deployment purpose — dev, staging, or prod — and BLOCKS for explicit operator confirmation, the same discipline as the dialect gate. No silent default: the skill never assumes prod-grade or dev-grade. The confirmed purpose then drives the defaults that hang on it — Azure DB for PostgreSQL tier/redundancy, backup retention, and which network/doorway posture is RECOMMENDED — but the skill surfaces purpose-appropriate options for the operator to confirm; the vault stays most-restrictive by default and any relaxation remains an explicit, surfaced decision (secure-by-default is preserved, not overridden).")
' @desc(USE-DEPLOY-ACCESS-CHECK, "Before writing the deployment diagram and IaC, /mdd-deploy runs an access-completeness pass over every secured store (Key Vault, the database, the registry, remote state): for each it must name who READS it and who WRITES/provisions it, each with an identity and a network path the chosen posture actually admits. A store that is read but never written, or a writer with no admitted path through a door the skill just locked, is a hole the skill SURFACES as a BLOCKING question — it never ships a diagram that only looks complete. It surfaces the connectivity options (e.g. allowlist / in-VNet / tunnel) framed by the deployment purpose; the operator chooses.")
' @desc(USE-DEPLOY-EXECUTE, "After planning, /mdd-deploy EXECUTES the generated runbook itself: it manages cloud auth (runs az login + selects/verifies the subscription, stopping if it is the wrong one), validates the IaC, runs a dry-run (terraform plan / az what-if) and shows the diff, then walks the runbook steps via Bash (az / terraform / docker). Idempotent and reversible steps (resource-group / ACR create, image build & push, plan/what-if, health checks) run AUTONOMOUSLY; the executor BLOCKS for an explicit operator confirmation only at IRREVERSIBLE steps — the first infra apply, secret writes into Key Vault, the migration job, and go-live. It HALTS on the first failed step (never barrels ahead), and deploys the new revision at 0% traffic until health checks pass so a bad rollout cannot take down the running revision. Constrained by OCL-DEPLOY-EXEC-DRYRUN-BEFORE-APPLY, -HALT-ON-ERROR, -PAUSE-IRREVERSIBLE.")
' @desc(USE-DEPLOY-GOLIVE, "The single mandatory stop even in full-auto: before routing live traffic and crossing the production billing multi-factor gate, /mdd-deploy surfaces the FULL gate state — ENABLE_PRODUCTION_BILLING, APP_ENV, DATABASE_MARKER, PUBLIC_HOST, APPLE_ENVIRONMENT, App Attest prod identity — and BLOCKS for an explicit operator confirmation. The go-live cutover is NEVER auto-confirmed; the operator confirms a live-money cutover with eyes open. Constrained by OCL-DEPLOY-EXEC-GOLIVE-CONFIRMED.")
title /mdd-deploy deployment guidance + execution — use cases (objective)

left to right direction

actor "Operator" as Op

rectangle "mdd toolchain (utility, outside the parity gate)" {
  usecase "PLAN then EXECUTE an Azure Container\nApps deployment: diagram + IaC +\nrunbook, then run it to live traffic" as Guide
  usecase "Choose & CONFIRM the IaC dialect\n(Bicep XOR Terraform) before any\nartifact is written — no silent default" as Dialect
  usecase "Confirm the deployment PURPOSE\n(dev/staging/prod) before any\npurpose-driven default — no silent default" as Purpose
  usecase "Account for who READS and WRITES\nevery secured store (identity + admitted\npath) before emitting — surface holes" as AccessCheck
  usecase "EXECUTE the runbook: manage auth,\ndry-run, apply, provision, migrate, route —\nautonomous except irreversible steps; halt on error" as Execute
  usecase "CONFIRM go-live: surface the full\nproduction billing multi-factor gate\nbefore live-traffic cutover" as GoLive
  usecase "Inspect the generated\ndeployment diagram as SVG" as Inspect
}

Op --> Guide
Op --> Dialect
Op --> Purpose
Op --> AccessCheck
Op --> Execute
Op --> GoLive
Op --> Inspect

Guide ..> Dialect : <<include>>
Guide ..> Purpose : <<include>>
Guide ..> AccessCheck : <<include>>
Guide ..> Execute : <<include>>
Execute ..> GoLive : <<include>>
Guide ..> Inspect : <<extend>>

note bottom of Guide
  v1 target: azure-container-apps (../atlas-ate-server).
  Reads .mdd/models + the target repo READ-ONLY to PLAN,
  then EXECUTES the runbook to live traffic. PAUSES with a
  BLOCKING clarification on ambiguity OR a GENERALIZED
  go-live landmine — any choice whose correctness depends
  on a fact NOT grounded in the inputs (app-config /
  purpose / access-path). Now RUNS az / terraform / docker
  via Bash; the old "executes nothing" non-goal is retired.
  Realized by SEQ-DEPLOY-GUIDANCE (plan) + SEQ-DEPLOY-EXECUTE (run).
end note

note bottom of Dialect
  Mandatory <<include>>: guidance cannot proceed until
  the dialect is explicitly confirmed. One per run
  (Bicep XOR Terraform). FULL PARITY — both enforce the
  identical invariant checklist + secure-by-default
  posture; only IaC structure differs.
  Realized by SEQ-DEPLOY-GUIDANCE.
end note

note bottom of Purpose
  Mandatory <<include>>: no purpose-driven default
  (DB tier/redundancy, backup retention, recommended
  doorway) is generated until dev/staging/prod is
  confirmed. No silent default; the skill never assumes
  prod- or dev-grade. Purpose RECOMMENDS; the operator
  confirms. Secure-by-default is preserved.
  Constrained by OCL-DEPLOY-IAC-PURPOSE /
  OCL-DEPLOY-IAC-SURFACE-NOT-DECIDE.
  Realized by SEQ-DEPLOY-GUIDANCE.
end note

note bottom of AccessCheck
  Mandatory <<include>>: before emitting, every secured
  store must have a named READER and WRITER, each with
  an admitted network path. A read-but-never-written
  store, or a writer with no admitted path, is SURFACED
  as a blocking question. Constrained by
  OCL-DEPLOY-IAC-ACCESS-COMPLETE / -SURFACE-NOT-DECIDE.
  Realized by SEQ-DEPLOY-GUIDANCE.
end note

note bottom of Execute
  Mandatory <<include>>: after planning, the skill walks
  the runbook itself. Manages auth (az login + subscription
  select), dry-runs before any apply, runs idempotent steps
  AUTONOMOUSLY, and BLOCKS only at irreversible steps
  (first apply, secret writes, migration, go-live). HALTS
  on first error; new revision at 0% traffic until verified.
  Constrained by OCL-DEPLOY-EXEC-DRYRUN-BEFORE-APPLY /
  -HALT-ON-ERROR / -PAUSE-IRREVERSIBLE.
  Realized by SEQ-DEPLOY-EXECUTE.
end note

note bottom of GoLive
  Mandatory <<include>> of Execute: the ONE stop that is
  never skipped in full-auto. Surfaces the full production
  billing multi-factor gate state, then BLOCKS for explicit
  operator confirmation before the live-traffic cutover.
  Never auto-confirmed. Constrained by
  OCL-DEPLOY-EXEC-GOLIVE-CONFIRMED.
  Realized by SEQ-DEPLOY-EXECUTE.
end note

note bottom of Inspect
  Not a gate. /mdd-validate, /mdd-review and the
  /mdd-cycle parity loop never read .mdd/deploy/.
  Realized by SEQ-DEPLOY-INSPECT.
end note
@enduml
